SUMMARY:Davis Farmers Market
DESCRIPTION:Year-round at Central Park in downtown Davis\, thousands gather each week to shop for what is grown\, raised\, and made locally at our markets. We are dedicated to bringing farmers right to your table\, so we stay open rain or shine. \nWalk rows of stalls lined with an array of fruits and vegetables\, including certified organic produce\, choice meats\, chicken\, seafood\, wine\, local eggs and honey. Choose from a variety of fresh-baked goods\, plants\, flowers and gifts. Enjoy a picnic from one of our many food stands\, made from market ingredients. \nSee the vendor list here: https://www.davisfarmersmarket.org/our-sellers/ \nFarmers Market Hours  \nCentral Park: Saturdays 8a–1p (year-round)\, and Wednesdays 3p–6p (September through March); 4p–8p (April through August)\nUC Davis – North Quad: Wednesdays 10a–1:30p (fall and spring quarters)\nSutter Davis Hospital: Thursdays 10a–1p (May through September)\nSutter Medical Center\, Sacramento: Thursdays 2:30p–5:30p \n 
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/davis-farmers-market-3-2-2-2/2026-04-04/
LOCATION:Central Park
CATEGORIES:Bring the Kids,Food & Drink,Shopping
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://thedirt.online/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/davis-farmers-market-logo-KERN-ADJUST2-01-1-e1649900473633.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Davis Farmers Market":MAILTO:dfmpr@dcn.org
END:VEVENT
