UID:10076776-1775293200-1775300400@thedirt.online
SUMMARY:Weave a Willow Bird Feeder
DESCRIPTION:Willow is a wonderful\, abundant riparian resource well-suited to weaving\, thanks to the strength and flexibility of its stems. In this workshop led by Natascha Paxton participants will learn a simple spiral weave technique to craft a small bird feeder out of ‘Sandbar Willow.’ Participants will also learn how to make their own vegan\, peanut-free bird seed balls to fill their feeders and support local birds. \nThis is a gentle\, beginner-friendly introduction to working with willow and an approachable first weaving project. If you are interested in working further with willow and advancing your weaving skills\, check out our upcoming Willow Basketry workshop with Samantha Iacobello! \nAll tools and materials will be provided. This workshop requires hand strength\, the ability to do repetitive hand movements\, and comfort sitting on the ground for extended periods of time. \nParticipants are encouraged to bring a cushion or low lawn chair for seating. You are welcome to bring your favorite utility or pocket knife and a set of pruning shears if you have either. \nAge 12+. \n 
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/weave-a-willow-bird-feeder/
CATEGORIES:Community,Outside
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://thedirt.online/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Bird-Feeder-Workshop_TheDirt.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Davis Forest School":MAILTO:programs@davisforestschool.org
END:VEVENT
